node.title: Police end latest search for William Tyrrell
node.description: Police hadÂ spent the last four weeks scouring areas near Kendall on the NSW Mid North Coast as they search for clues into the missing toddler.
node.content:
["The renewed search for missing toddler William Tyrell has ended on the NSW Mid North Coast.", "Around 30 police officers and detectives spent more than four weeks scouring bushland and waterways\u00a0near\u00a0Kendall, south of Port Macquarie, where the three year old was last seen on September 19, 2014.\u00a0", "Red, blue and black cloth as well as other items were found but none have been linked to the three year old's disappearance.", "The toddler was last seen playing in a Spider-Man suit outside his foster grandmother's home on Benaroon Drive at Kendall\u00a0seven years ago.\u00a0", "", "
Emergency services finshing up at the search site for William Tyrrell at Kendall, NSW.\u00a0(ABC Mid North Coast: Luisa Rubbo)
", "During the latest search\u00a0a\u00a0car, which belonged to the boy's late foster grandmother, was also seized by police\u00a0from Gymea in Sydney's south on November 9.", "Police believe the car may have been used to transfer the boy's body.\u00a0", "New evidence from the operation is expected to be put before the coronial inquest, which is set to resume at a later date.", "More to come.\u00a0", "", "
A rake, signed by emergency services involved in the search, has been erected as a memorial at the search site.\u00a0\u00a0(ABC Mid North Coast: Luisa Rubbo)
"]
